@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>The Disaster Alleviation Foundation ("we," "our," "us") is committed to protecting the privacy of our donors, volunteers, and beneficiaries. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you interact with our systems and services.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect various types of information to provide and improve our services:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Information</strong>: This includes names, contact details, and other identifying information provided by donors, volunteers, and beneficiaries.</li>
    <li><strong>Donation Information</strong>: Details about donations, including the type (goods or monetary), amount, date, and donor preferences (e.g., anonymity).</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data</strong>: Information on how our systems are accessed and used, including IP addresses, browser types, and usage patterns.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>To Track Donations</strong>: Ensuring that all donations are accurately recorded and dispatched to the appropriate disaster relief efforts.</li>
    <li><strong>To Communicate</strong>: Keeping donors, volunteers, and beneficiaries informed about our activities, needs, and impact.</li>
    <li><strong>To Improve Our Services</strong>: Analyzing usage data to enhance our systems and services.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
<p>We may share your information in the following situations:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>With Your Consent</strong>: We may disclose your information with your explicit consent.</li>
    <li><strong>For Legal Reasons</strong>: If required by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</li>
    <li><strong>To Protect Our Rights</strong>: When necessary to protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property, and that of our users and the public.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Security</h2>
<p>We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

<h2>Your Privacy Choices</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Access Your Information</strong>: Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.</li>
    <li><strong>Update Your Information</strong>: Correct any inaccuracies in your personal information.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete Your Information</strong>: Request the deletion of your personal information, subject to legal and operational requirements.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our website. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.</p>

<h2>Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
<p>
    The Disaster Alleviation Foundation<br />
    [Contact Information]
</p>
